    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The error you have is because the container is not running erigon as root internally, but as a regular user `erigon` with UID/GID 1000, which is preferred for security reasons. You can see this user being created in the [Dockerfile](https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/blob/devel/Dockerfile).\r\n\r\nWhen it comes to mounted volumes, docker maps the container's users to the host's users using their UID/GID. If there is no UID/GID match, or if the mapped host user has no right over the host's folder that you're mounting, you will get a permission denied error. \r\n\r\nI fixed it by giving a host's user ownership of the folder, where the host's user UID/GID is the same as the docker's user UID/GID (1000).\r\n\r\nMore details in this [post](https://www.fullstaq.com/knowledge-hub/blogs/docker-and-the-host-filesystem-owner-matching-problem).\r\n",
